<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="104" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,289,746]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,613,638]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species somewhat resembles Genus two species d (
<bibRefCitation box="[948,1084,613,638]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" refId="ref16205" refString="Sweet, M. H. (1996) The Evolution of the Haustorioidea of the World, and Post-Embryonic Development, Taxonomy and Ecology of the Haustoriidae (Amphipoda: Crustacea). Texas A &amp; M University, College Station, 640 pp. [PhD thesis]" type="book">Sweet 1996</bibRefCitation>
), which was also sampled from the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[280,383,650,673]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
, except that in 
<taxonomicName box="[552,704,650,673]" class="Malacostraca" family="Haustoriidae" genus="Haustorius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[552,704,650,673]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">H. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the uropod 1 peduncle is largely bare and the coxa of pereopod 5 is oval, without distinct lobes. This could indicate that at least one species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock &amp; Wicksten" authorityYear="2018" box="[1013,1138,686,709]" class="Malacostraca" family="Haustoriidae" genus="Haustorius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1013,1138,686,709]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Haustorius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains undescribed from the east coast of 
<collectingRegion box="[337,426,721,746]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">
<collectingCountry box="[337,426,721,746]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Mexico</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
